completionOptions.mergeCommitMessage:
Merged PR 155698: Publish project as a package

## Summary
- This PR will reconfigure the project to be published as a package instead of deploying as a federated module so it can be used in AEM projects.
- Shadow mode will need to be added to a project's dependencies in package.json and used like a normal component.
- It uses simpler dependencies and it's now simpler to include in other projects
- instead of environment variables, a graphqlUrl prop must be provided at runtime
- we lose the convenience of a single shadow mode deployment updating every consumer app. every consumer will have to individually deploy every shadow mode update.

## Details

Federated module tooling didn't work out. AEM doesn't support federated modules. 
1. Without support from Vercel, I don't expect support to improve for NextJS. 
2. Webpack was the main supporter of module federation, and Webpack is losing out to other build tools.
3. Given the state of JavaScript and rapid ecosystem changes, the future of module federation is uncertain.

CRACO was removed because create react app is no longer supported. Vite is used to build shadow mode as a library instead.

To improve integration with the old shadow mode implementation, cookie storage is used instead of the relay store. Relay ended up being less useful for shadow mode, so relay was replaced with react-query and graphql-request. The code was simplified as a result, and now future projects won't have to use Relay to use shadow mode. An optional onSubmit handler was added to customise shadow mode's behaviour.

Upgrading AEM to react 18 is expected to take some effort. graphql-request v3.39 is used because it doesn't require react 18 like '@tanstack/react-query' v5 does. 

In the absence of relay, [graphql codegen](https://the-guild.dev/graphql/codegen) was added for the graphql code generation. the __gql__ directory contains code generated by graphql codegen.

Instead of using build time variables, graphqlUrl will need to be supplied at run time.

feature flags were removed.

Related work items: #2719410, #2733837

description:
## Summary
- This PR will reconfigure the project to be published as a package instead of deploying as a federated module so it can be used in AEM projects.
- Shadow mode will need to be added to a project's dependencies in package.json and used like a normal component.
- It uses simpler dependencies and it's now simpler to include in other projects
- instead of environment variables, a graphqlUrl
title: Publish project as a package
